                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>vain for your Sermon in the Presbyterian, and I have<lb/> received\n                                        no private reply. It is notwithstanding due to the<lb/>\n                                        liberality of this Editor to say that he immediately\n                                        pub-<lb/>lished <persName>Dr. Schelsinger's</persName>\n                                        Reply. I next wrote to the Editor<lb/> of the New York\n                                        Observer, but I am sorry to say I never<lb/> received any\n                                        reply. I have written to other editors whose<lb/>\n                                        publications are read by all the members of the Synod,<lb/>\n                                        and without yet promising unconditionally to publish\n                                        your<lb/> Sermon, they raise questions about its length\n                                        &amp;c. and say<lb/> they wish first to see it. So I hope I\n                                        can accomplish<lb/> what you request, if you will send your\n                                        Sermon to me<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>122 Broome street</placeName>. Please have it\n                                        carefully and plainly<lb/> written, and if it should be very\n                                        long perhaps you would<lb/> not object to dividing it in the\n                                        publication. For my<lb/> letters to the Editors I have urged\n                                        as well as I could,<lb/> that we have read too much about\n                                        the Jews from Christi-<lb/>ans and proselytes and that it is\n                                        an act of justice<lb/> which we owe to them to let them\n                                        explain themselves<lb/> in our hearing. So I will expect\n                                        soon to re-<lb/>ceive your sermon.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am very willing to write in the next volume<lb/>\n                                        of the Occident as you propose, and to occupy as much<lb/>\n                                        space as you can give me, but perhaps it would<lb/> be\n                                        better to form some plan before we commence<lb/> Perhaps you\n                                        would assign to me a certain number of<lb/> letters or a\n                                        certain portion of your space and to an<lb/> opponent the\n                                        same. If a place were thus formed and</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zw19c53/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
